<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,1532,2025]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,320,1532,1557]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Identification.</emphasis>
Forewing length 
<number box="[517,551,1533,1557]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" value="8.5">8.5</number>
–10.0 mm. 
<taxonomicName box="[680,947,1534,1557]" class="Insecta" family="Noctuidae" genus="Hyperstrotia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="18" pageNumber="19" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pervertens">
<emphasis box="[680,947,1534,1557]" italics="true" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Hyperstrotia pervertens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a light gray, nondescript moth. Forewing with white antemedial and postmedial lines (some specimens may have a thin black line associated with these white lines), reniform spot a small black dot, and outer margin with small dark gray elongate spots. 
<collectingCountry box="[1289,1345,1605,1629]" name="India" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Hind</collectingCountry>
wing is light gray.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="18.[151,1436,1532,2025]" box="[197,726,1676,1702]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,360,1676,1701]" pageId="18" pageNumber="19">Flight period.</emphasis>
End of May to early September.
</paragraph>
